headline: Goldman Sachs Upgrades Cummins (CMI) Stock to Buy, Raises PT
summary: On May 27, analysts at Goldman Sachs upped Cummins Inc. (NYSE:CMI)’s stock from “Neutral” to “Buy,” raising its price objective to $431 from the prior target of $410. This upgrade stems from the expectations of structurally higher profitability in the company’s Power Systems business, thanks to the new pricing structure extending beyond data centers. The […]

headline: Goldman Sachs: Machinery supply is improving for the first time in three years
summary: Investing.com -- Goldman Sachs has upgraded Cummins Inc (NYSE:CMI). to Buy from Neutral, citing a turning point in machinery supply trends and improving fundamentals in the company’s Power Systems division.
